EnergyDepositionThreshold.desc: All hits with smaller energy will be dropped at SensitiveDetector level

MinTrackLength.desc: Min. track length required for saving in MCParticle.; to be applied to all particles other than primaries and decay-daughters.

GlobalPhiRotation.desc: Global rotation in phi; valid only for sense wires now.

ClockFrequencyForTDC.desc: Frequency (GHz) of the clock used for TDC, where 1.017774 GHz is 2 x (accelerator's RF).

MaterialDefinitionMode.desc: =0: define a mixture of gases and wires in the entire tracking volume; =1: dummy (unavailable now); =2: define all sense and field wires explicitly in the volume.

SenseWireZposMode.desc: =0: no corr.; =1: corr. for feedthrough effect and for diff. betw. new- and old-design (tentative).

deltazFileName.desc: file which contains corrs. for diff. betw. final- and old-design.

Debug.desc: true: print out; false: not print out.

XTetc.desc: true: load x-t etc. params. from disk; false: not load.

Displacement.desc: true: load displacements for sense wires; false: not.

Misalignment.desc: true: load misalignments for sense wires; false: not.

Alignment.desc: true: load alignments for sense wires; false: not.

XTetc4Recon.desc: true: use calibrated x-t etc.; false: use the same ones as used in simulation

xt4ReconFileName.desc: file which contains x-t relation for reconstruction

sigma4ReconFileName.desc: file which contains space resol. for reconstruction

propSpeed4ReconFileName.desc: file which contains propagation speed for reconstruction

t04ReconFileName.desc: file which contains t0 for reconstruction

tw4ReconFileName.desc: file which contains time-walk for reconstruction

OffsetZ.desc: The offset of the whole cdc in z with respect to the IP (should be the same as beampipe)

NShift.desc: the shifted hole number of each wire in this layer

Offset.desc: wire offset in phi direction at endplate
